<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width;">
    <style>
        /* Mobile styles (default) */
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            
            background: #f0f0f0;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
 justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
        }
h1 {
font-size: 2rem;
}
.container img {
display: block;
  margin: auto;
  width: 40%;
}
        .container {
            background: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
 justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
        }


        /* Desktop styles (screens wider than 768px) */
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            body {
                background: #d1d1d1;
               /* display: inline-block;*/
                justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
width:90%;
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
            }
.container img {
display: block;
  margin: auto;
  width: 40%;
}
            .container {
                width: 100%; /* Mimics a fixed window feel */
                box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
margin-left: auto;
margin-right: auto;
 justify-content: center;
align-items: center;
            }
        }


.flex-container h2 {
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
border-radius: 8px;
width: 45%;
margin-left:2%; 
margin-right:2%;
font-size: 1.5rem;
margin-top: 5%;
margin-bottom: 5%;
}

.flex-container {
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
border-radius: 8px;
background: white;
margin: 3%;
margin-top: 5%;
margin-bottom: 5%;
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap; /* Allows items to wrap to the next line */
 /* gap: 5%;  Optional: Adds space between the items */
/*  justify-content: space-between;  Optional: Distributes space evenly */
}

.flex-container img {
box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
border-radius: 8px;
  /* Calculates width to be less than 50% to leave room for the gap */
  width: calc(50% - 5px); 
  height: auto;
  /* Ensures padding and border are included in the width calculation */
  box-sizing: border-box; 
  /* Ensures images maintain aspect ratio and fill space nicely */
  object-fit: cover;
margin-top: 5%;
margin-bottom: 5%;
}

    </style>
</head>
<body>
 <div class="container">
        <h1 style="text-align:center">Field Report</h1>
<h2>We are please to present the following report</p>
        
<p>Address: <br> 2362 Wyecroft Road Unit 2<br>Oakvile, Ontario<br>L6L 6M1</p>
<p>Date Submited: March 3, 2026</p>
<p>This is just a quick template that I put together, something really basic. This would eliminate the need to email photos and descriptions separate<br>as it can be accessed from the office or on the road, I would have to build a login page to ensure only people with the proper credentials are able<br>to view the reports submitted<br><br></p>
<p>You can play around with the template if you would like, photo and description is required or else the system rejects the upload.</p>
<hr>
<form action="/home" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
            
              <label for="image">Upload Image</label>
              <input type="file" id="image" name="image" accept="image/*" required />
                <label for="description"><br>Description: </label>
                <input type="text" id="description" name="description" required />

                <id="address" name="address" />

            <p></p>
            
<button type="submit" onclick="window.Android.showToast('Button clicked!')">Submit</button>
                
            <p><br></p>
        </form>
</hr>
</div>
<div class="container">
<% if (items.length > 0) { %>
            <% items.forEach(item => { %>
             
                    <img src="data:<%= item.img.contentType %>;base64,<%= item.img.data.toString('base64') %>"/>
<p style="text-align:center; padding-left:10%; padding-right:10%;"><%= item.img.description %><br><br></p>
                
            <% }); %>
        <% } %>
</div>
<div class="flex-container">  

<% if (items.length > 0) { %>
            <% items.forEach(item => { %>
           
                    <img src="data:<%= item.img.contentType %>;base64,<%= item.img.data.toString('base64') %>"/>
<h2><%= item.img.description %><br><br></h2>
               
            <% }); %>
        <% } %>
</div> 
</body>
</html>
